;     transformer-backprop now returns 127 three-way: the REVERSE pass over the transformer's affine node
;     (the workhorse of every q/k/v/out projection and FFN layer in transformer-block.fk) — db = gy,
;     dW = outer(gy, x), and the chain dx = Wᵀ·gy (bit-exact) — composed with an SGD update generalized
;     from form-train-step.fk's one-weight atom to a whole weight MATRIX and bias VECTOR. The band trains
;     a 2→2 affine from W=0 to fit a target with strictly decreasing loss, the dx chain and dW outer both
