;     3-kernel only (Go=Rust=TS), the SAME floor transformer-block is proven on (the transformer op family
;     is not in the fourth-arm manifest). This is the autodiff-gradient-cell wall, opened at the affine
;     node. The gelu' vjp is now built too: the FFN sub-block y = W2·gelu(W1·x+b1)+b2 trains by backprop
;     THROUGH the nonlinearity (dh1 = da ⊙ gelu'(h1), gelu' composed from tn-tanh) — a 2→2→2 MLP fits a
;     target with strictly decreasing loss, gelu'(0)=0.5 / gelu'(1)=1.082964 / gelu'(-0.75)=0.001062 (the
;     dip) pinned bit-exact, tests/transformer-backprop-ffn-band.fk → 63 FOUR-WAY (Go=Rust=TS=fkwu).
;     The softmax' and layernorm' gradient nodes are now built too (transformer-backprop-softmax-ln-band.fk
;     → 31 FOUR-WAY), each proven by its own CONSERVATION LAW: softmax' has Σdz=0 (mass conserved, exact),
;     layernorm' has Σdx=0 (mean-orthogonal, exact) and <dx,y>≈0 (scale-orthogonal to ~4e-6, the eps/Newton
;     residual named honestly). So EVERY node of transformer-block.fk's pre-LN block now has its backward —
;     affine (127), gelu (63), softmax+layernorm (31). The whole proven forward block can train end to end.
;     The FFN-residual half is now ASSEMBLED and trained: y = h + FFN(LN(h)), backward dh = dy + LN'(FFN_in(dy))
;     — the gradient HIGHWAY composing affine vjp + gelu' + layernorm' + the residual. A two-block FFN-residual
;     STACK trains end to end (transformer-block-backward-band.fk → 31, Go=Rust=TS; 3-kernel-only by the
;     fkwu TABLE-CAPACITY wall — the 150-step two-block SGD loop overflows the walker's pre-flattened table,
;     a segfault, NOT a value divergence and NOT a missing op family; its constituent node gradients all
;     cross four-way in isolation, so the wall is table size, not the math — same wall as the assembly band):
;     loss 0.814 → ~0, and the LOWER block's weights move off their init, so dh chained correctly through
;     layernorm' (a wrong dh would have starved it). The ATTENTION CORE backward is now built too — the steepest gradient, through the
;     softmax-weighted value mixing: dv_j = α_j·dout (the value-grads PARTITION dout — Σdv = dout exactly,
;     since Σα = 1), dα = <dout,v>, ds = softmax'(α,dα), dq = scale·Σ ds_j·k_j. Proven by the partition law
;     (exact) AND by training a query to steer attention onto a target in the values' convex hull, loss → 0
;     (transformer-attention-backward-band.fk → 31 FOUR-WAY). So EVERY gradient NODE the transformer needs
;     now crosses FOUR-WAY: affine (127), gelu (63), softmax+layernorm (31), attention core (31) — the whole
;     backward floor at the node level on Go/Rust/TS/fkwu, matching the four-way forward floor (numerics 4095,
;     block 511). The assembled end-to-end TRAINING stacks (FFN-residual block-backward 31, the heterogeneous
;     assembly 63) stay 3-kernel-only on the fkwu table-capacity wall above — table size, not the math. And
;     the ASSEMBLY is now done: the FULL transformer block trains end to end. A LAYER is a
;     typed cell with a uniform (fwd, step) interface; a heterogeneous STACK — an attention-residual layer
;     THEN an FFN-residual layer, the actual tb-block — trains through ONE generic engine (tbp-stk-fwd /
;     tbp-stk-step with type dispatch). transformer-block-assembly-band.fk → 63, Go=Rust=TS (3-kernel-only,
;     the same fkwu table-capacity wall as block-backward): the block's
;     forward is deterministic, the stack converges (loss 0.71 → 0 in ~50 steps), and BOTH heterogeneous
;     layers learn (the attention layer's Wq and the FFN layer's W1 both move off their inits), so the
;     gradient chains correctly BETWEEN different layer types. This is auto-ml's assembly knowledge realized:
;     the architecture is a SEQUENCE of typed layer-cells, the dynamic-recipe advantage applied to the
;     transformer — the same shape recipe-gen.fk uses to compose experts now composes LAYERS into a trained
;     block, so the generator can assemble and configure architectures, not just hand-built ones. Adam itself
;     is already built FOUR-WAY in the sibling scalar lane below (adam-step-cell / adam-bias-correction,
;     fixed-point), so the optimizer beyond SGD exists; remaining is wiring that Adam onto these fp64 tensor
;     gradients, the full T-position sequence self-attention (k/v also projected, cross-query gradient
;     accumulation), and the convergence — a trainable transformer-block layer as an MoE expert kind, trained
;     by this backward on the GPU. (These fp64 tensor gradients are the TENSOR-SCALE autodiff wall the scalar
;     tensor-autodiff-verifier below names as separate — now opened, three-way.)
;     AND IT RUNS ON METAL. jit-tensor-emit.fk now emits that training step as an MSL kernel
;     (jte-affine-train-msl — one GPU thread per output row: forward dot in tb-dot's downward fold, then
;     g = 2(y-t) and the in-place SGD update row -= lr·g·x, b -= lr·g). The emitter is a Form recipe,
;     byte-stable three-way: tests/affine-train-emit-band.fk → 7. LIVE WITNESS scripts/metal_backprop_audit.sh
;     on this M4 Max compiles the emitted kernel and trains a real affine on the GPU: 32×32 loss 126→0,
;     bit-exact vs the fp32 CPU reference (max|ΔW|=0); 1280×1280 (whisper-large d_model, 1.64M params) loss
;     5115→2.2e-8 in 200 steps at 1.054 ms/step, GPU loss matching the fp32 CPU reference to 9 sig figs
;     (ΔW within fp32 epsilon — GPU FMA vs CPU split-mul). The fp64 recipe is the proven algorithm; the
;     fp32 MSL is its GPU carrier, conformance-gated in the lane's own semantics. The learning kernel runs
;     on the silicon — host-kernel.form's "drive the organ" realized for backprop.
;     AND NOW THE FFN CORE TRAINS ON METAL, not just one affine. jit-tensor-emit.fk emits
;     jte-mlp-train-msl — the FFN-core training step y = W2·gelu(W1·x + b1) + b2 (tbp-mlp-step, the two-layer
;     MLP inside the architect's block) as ONE Metal kernel run by a single threadgroup with barriered phases. The
;     transcendental is the recipe's OWN: the kernel's gelu/gelu' compose from fexp (tn-exp's 14-term
;     square-and-reduce Taylor) and ftanh ((e^2x-1)/(e^2x+1)), so the GPU walks transformer-numerics.fk's
;     approximation, never Metal's tanh(). The two forward matvecs carry tb-dot's downward right-fold; the
;     dh1 column reduction carries tbp-wt-gy-acc's forward left-fold; the residual-free block forces one
;     ordering rule — dh1 (phase 3) reads the OLD W2 before phase 4 overwrites it, so a threadgroup_barrier
;     between phases makes the single-group read-then-write deterministic. The emitter is a Form recipe,
;     byte-stable three-way: tests/mlp-train-emit-band.fk → 7. LIVE WITNESS scripts/metal_ffn_audit.sh on
;     this M4 Max compiles the emitted kernel and trains a real FFN (in=256, hid=384, out=256, 197,248
;     params): loss 46.26 → 5.9e-16 in 25 steps at 0.40 ms/step, the GPU weights matching an fp32 CPU mirror
;     of the same phases to max|ΔW|=6.1e-6 — within fp32 epsilon (the recipe's exp squares a Taylor value up
;     to k times, so a 1-ULP divide difference is amplified by the squaring, not a wrong fold). The fp64
;     recipe is the proven algorithm; the fp32 MSL is its GPU carrier.
;     AND THE ARCHITECT'S CAPACITY SEARCH NOW RUNS ON THE SILICON. jte-resid-train-msl emits the architect's
;     ACTUAL layer — the pre-LN residual block y = h + (W2·gelu(W1·LN(h)+b1)+b2), tbp-stk-step on one "ffn"
;     layer, exactly what ac-ffn-layer builds and ac-train trains. It is the FFN-core kernel wrapped with the
;     two pieces the residual block adds: a pre-LN of the input (z = LN(h) by thread 0, tn-mean/tn-var/tn-sqrt's
;     exact folds — biased variance, eps inside a 50-iteration Newton sqrt) and the residual highway (y = h+ffn,
;     so gy = 2(y-t) flows straight to the FFN as gout); the FFN reads z and the W1 update uses z. Byte-stable
;     three-way: tests/resid-train-emit-band.fk → 7. LIVE WITNESS scripts/metal_arch_search_audit.sh runs
;     arch-capacity.fk's ac-min-width ON THE GPU: on the d=4 reversal dataset it trains each candidate width
;     (1..4) over the dataset on the M4 Max and crowns the smallest that fits — width 1 underfits (loss 7.6),
;     width 2 fits (loss 4.8e-7), crown = 2. THREE executions, ONE crown: the fp64 Form recipe ac-min-width
;     (arch-capacity-band → 31), the fp32 GPU, and the fp32 CPU mirror all crown width 2 — the architect timing
;     real candidates on the silicon, capacity discovered, not assumed. The huge underfit gap makes the crown
;     robust to fp32. The architect's layer learns on the silicon and the search now runs there too.
;     AND THE TYPE AXIS IS NOW COVERED ON THE GPU: jte-attn-train-msl emits the architect's OTHER layer kind —
;     the cross-attention-residual block h = x + Wo·attend(Wq·LN(x), ks, vs, scale), tbp-layer-step on an "attn"
;     layer, updating Wq and Wo. It composes every attention-core gradient (softmax-back, the dv partition, the
;     dq weighted-key sum) plus the pre-LN and the residual highway, with the recipe's exact folds (tb-dot
;     downward, the attention sums forward, tn-max-subtract softmax over the recipe's own fexp). Byte-stable
;     three-way: tests/attn-train-emit-band.fk → 7. LIVE WITNESS scripts/metal_attn_audit.sh trains a d=4,
;     3-key attention layer on the M4 Max: loss 2.72 → 1.8e-12 in 200 steps at 0.24 ms/step, the GPU weights
;     within fp32 epsilon (max|ΔW|=3.0e-7) of the fp32 CPU mirror. Both architect layer kinds — FFN-residual and
;     attention-residual — now train on the silicon, so arch-search's full (depth × width × TYPE) grid can be
;     timed on the GPU. The attention kernel runs the small per-key/projection work in one thread; parallelizing
;     across keys and projection rows is the named follow-up.
